cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.GT, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with geometric algorithms and optimization, which suggests that it could belong to cs.CG (Computational Geometry) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The problem of partitioning point sets using hyperplanes is also related to discrete mathematics, which makes cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) a likely category as well. The use of submodular optimization algorithms suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.GT (Game Theory) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
